    "Indeed, these methods are not in any way tied to any regulatory framework that offers the citizen to reason about how the captured data is used.",
    "Finally, these methods require active citizen participation, either by installing detectors on their home windows (in the case of Wi-Fly [18]) or physically perturbing the object/citizen suspected of being observed (in the case of Nassi et al. 's work [17,67,68]).",
    "However, some synergies with Privadome exist.",
